        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>John Stevens Henslow was a British botanist and taught mineralogy (1822-1827) and botany (1827-1861) at Cambridge. It was he who recommended his pupil Charles Robert Darwin as naturalist for the Beagle expedition, 1831-1836.</p>
        </bioghist>
